1
00:00:00,273 --> 00:00:01,593
Tash, are we live?

2
00:00:02,160 --> 00:00:04,300
Yes, Andres!

3
00:00:04,733 --> 00:00:09,480
And we’re here to take you guys
to a super cute activity today!

4
00:00:09,505 --> 00:00:11,343
Wait a second. Why is it cute?

5
00:00:11,523 --> 00:00:12,889
Give them a clue.
Can we give them a clue?

6
00:00:12,914 --> 00:00:15,668
Andres, I’m not sure if we
want to reveal it so soon,

7
00:00:15,692 --> 00:00:18,446
because we want it to be a
surprise for Mom and Dad!

8
00:00:18,612 --> 00:00:22,475
But, for a clue,
it’s about a tattoo.

9
00:00:23,108 --> 00:00:24,675
What?! What, what, what?! A tattoo?!

10
00:00:25,184 --> 00:00:26,471
Wait a minute! My love!

11
00:00:26,668 --> 00:00:29,336
My love!
The kids are getting tattoos!

12
00:00:29,361 --> 00:00:31,700
Mom, mom, mom, wait, wait!
It’s not what you’re thinking!

13
00:00:32,253 --> 00:00:33,253
Hey!

14
00:00:35,062 --> 00:00:37,458
- The kids are going to get tattoos!
- What is this talk I hear about tattoos?!

15
00:00:37,483 --> 00:00:39,168
‘Fess up, who’s going to get tattoos?

16
00:00:39,879 --> 00:00:41,406
Okay, let’s just put it this way.

17
00:00:41,717 --> 00:00:43,557
Let’s start from the beginning.

18
00:01:44,809 --> 00:01:46,743
I’ll go ahead.
I have somewhere I need to be.

19
00:01:47,451 --> 00:01:49,364
You’re walking?
I thought you’re unable to walk.

20
00:01:49,481 --> 00:01:52,074
Oh, sometimes I do.
But today, I’m rolling, look.

21
00:01:52,105 --> 00:01:54,057
Oh, rolling. You’re funny.

22
00:01:54,082 --> 00:01:56,108
See, I was just kidding.
Alright, I’ll go ahead now, really.

23
00:01:56,626 --> 00:01:59,926
Hey, hey, hey! You might fall!
Cap! Here, to the right, to the right!

24
00:01:59,973 --> 00:02:01,053
Oh those humps are too steep!

25
00:02:02,172 --> 00:02:03,512
- Look at you.
- Aga!

26
00:02:04,072 --> 00:02:05,812
Oh hey, Chef K!

27
00:02:05,837 --> 00:02:07,443
It’s a happy day!

28
00:02:07,468 --> 00:02:08,468
Of course!

29
00:02:10,291 --> 00:02:11,576
Oh, is it your birthday?

30
00:02:11,601 --> 00:02:12,734
Happy Birthday!

31
00:02:13,001 --> 00:02:14,001
Nope.

32
00:02:14,665 --> 00:02:16,845
Bake K Naman’s
happy anniversary?

33
00:02:17,077 --> 00:02:19,264
No! You’re annoying!

34
00:02:19,289 --> 00:02:23,871
So, what is it?
Letter D! As in Debt!

35
00:02:24,882 --> 00:02:27,145
Debt.

36
00:02:28,739 --> 00:02:29,979
Pay up.

37
00:02:30,126 --> 00:02:32,546
Right. I’m sorry.

38
00:02:34,801 --> 00:02:36,034
That’s what I’ve been saying.

39
00:02:38,028 --> 00:02:41,382
Can I pay you by
the end of this month?

40
00:02:41,997 --> 00:02:43,277
Oh, heck no.

41
00:02:43,302 --> 00:02:44,302
Next month?

42
00:02:44,327 --> 00:02:46,358
It would be fine if it was just me,
but it isn’t.

43
00:02:46,597 --> 00:02:48,137
I owe this money from a friend.

44
00:02:48,203 --> 00:02:49,297
It’s complicated.

45
00:02:49,450 --> 00:02:51,603
You know what,
let me tell you something,

46
00:02:52,424 --> 00:02:56,477
in this barangay, we know that
you’re really the one lending the money.

47
00:02:56,502 --> 00:02:59,189
We know that,
you don’t have to lie about it.

48
00:03:00,322 --> 00:03:01,722
Why don’t you just say it.

49
00:03:01,773 --> 00:03:02,863
Okay, okay, fine, fine, fine.

50
00:03:02,887 --> 00:03:04,845
I’ll confess, okay.
It’s me, I lend the money.

51
00:03:05,043 --> 00:03:08,637
That’s the reason why I get embarrassed
going around asking for payment.

52
00:03:08,669 --> 00:03:12,028
Don’t be embarrassed!
We appreciate everything that you do.

53
00:03:12,053 --> 00:03:13,734
Don’t be embarrassed, that’s okay!

54
00:03:13,759 --> 00:03:15,105
- I shouldn’t be embarrassed?
- Of course!

55
00:03:15,130 --> 00:03:16,318
You’re going to ask them to pay?

56
00:03:16,620 --> 00:03:19,708
Yeah! Pay up!
Now! Pay up now!

57
00:03:19,733 --> 00:03:21,172
Please have mercy on me.

58
00:03:21,283 --> 00:03:22,603
Mercy?

59
00:03:22,628 --> 00:03:24,893
- Yeah!
- Oh wow. How come?

60
00:03:26,293 --> 00:03:31,433
Did you have mercy
when you stole Chacha from me?

61
00:03:33,001 --> 00:03:34,275
Did you feel so?

62
00:03:34,596 --> 00:03:40,663
And do you really think
I’d give your feelings a chance,

63
00:03:40,695 --> 00:03:44,040
when you didn’t
give mine a chance?

64
00:03:45,228 --> 00:03:47,395
Mercy?! What Mercy?!

65
00:03:49,206 --> 00:03:54,099
Wait, hold on a second.
You two sound serious!

66
00:03:54,124 --> 00:03:55,348
- Chacha!
- Yes?

67
00:03:55,378 --> 00:03:58,472
Well, listen to this guy.
He’s asking me to pay my debts completely.

68
00:03:58,519 --> 00:03:59,519
- Hey!
- What?

69
00:03:59,544 --> 00:04:03,511
What the heck are you saying,
what are you thinking?

70
00:04:03,603 --> 00:04:05,839
I never said
I was asking you to pay up!

71
00:04:05,964 --> 00:04:07,515
I was just walking by, Chacha,

72
00:04:07,539 --> 00:04:09,179
and then he suddenly felt
compelled to talk about his debt,

73
00:04:09,218 --> 00:04:11,403
and I told him not
to worry about it!

74
00:04:11,748 --> 00:04:13,294
What do you mean not to
worry about it? Because?

75
00:04:13,319 --> 00:04:16,156
You don’t have to worry about it because
you can pay me at the end of the month!

76
00:04:17,386 --> 00:04:20,863
Oh, wow! Thank you, Chef K!
Thank you so much, really!

77
00:04:21,803 --> 00:04:23,898
Chacha, it’s just that I feel offended.

78
00:04:24,155 --> 00:04:25,468
He was shouting at me.

79
00:04:25,669 --> 00:04:26,669
He was?

80
00:04:26,694 --> 00:04:27,880
- I wasn’t!
- You were shouting at him?!

81
00:04:27,925 --> 00:04:29,250
Chef K, was I shouting at you?!

82
00:04:29,293 --> 00:04:32,763
- I wish you weren’t!
- He was asking me to pay up!

83
00:04:32,788 --> 00:04:34,170
Don’t shout at him, my love!

84
00:04:35,261 --> 00:04:36,441
- Oh!
- Two points!

85
00:04:38,724 --> 00:04:41,043
Hey, be careful!

86
00:04:41,297 --> 00:04:42,668
If I get hit by then,

87
00:04:42,692 --> 00:04:45,504
I will slap each one of you,
you’ll see!

88
00:04:46,155 --> 00:04:50,472
If I get hit by that,
I will slap each one of you!

89
00:04:54,151 --> 00:04:55,424
- Ow!
- I’m sorry!

90
00:04:55,791 --> 00:04:57,108
- Wait.
- Andy?!

91
00:04:57,133 --> 00:04:58,133
Keila?!

92
00:04:58,881 --> 00:05:00,361
How are you?!

93
00:05:00,386 --> 00:05:01,838
I’m good, I’m good!
How are you?!

94
00:05:01,863 --> 00:05:03,588
Are you back from Singapore?

95
00:05:03,666 --> 00:05:06,054
- Uh…
- You never told me!

96
00:05:06,553 --> 00:05:08,053
So, what’s up?
What’s keeping you busy now?

97
00:05:08,078 --> 00:05:12,643
Um, nothing much,
just an influencer with a 500k following!

98
00:05:12,668 --> 00:05:14,733
Oh wow, five hundred?! That’s great!

99
00:05:14,758 --> 00:05:16,173
- Follow me, alright?
- Of course, I will!

100
00:05:16,228 --> 00:05:19,234
Ah, Tash!
This is Keila, my classmate.

101
00:05:20,046 --> 00:05:21,046
This is Tash.

102
00:05:21,454 --> 00:05:23,207
Anne, remember our classmate Keila?

103
00:05:23,491 --> 00:05:24,491
Of course, I do!

104
00:05:24,742 --> 00:05:29,525
Who’s ever going to forget her
with her screaming pink outfits!

105
00:05:31,138 --> 00:05:32,138
Hi, Anne!

106
00:05:32,408 --> 00:05:33,948
You look… the same.

107
00:05:33,973 --> 00:05:35,335
Just the same.

108
00:05:35,703 --> 00:05:37,383
Which is… which is good!

109
00:05:38,782 --> 00:05:40,711
Hi, Pink…
I mean Kayla!

110
00:05:40,755 --> 00:05:44,991
I’m Andres’ sister who’s
now focused on pastries.

111
00:05:45,976 --> 00:05:48,082
Do you wanna try our bread?

112
00:05:48,107 --> 00:05:50,310
Mmm! We have bread!
Would you like some?

113
00:05:50,335 --> 00:05:52,254
Uh, what do you have?

114
00:05:52,569 --> 00:05:53,569
Show me!

115
00:05:53,594 --> 00:05:56,839
Pandesal, other breads, ensaymada!

116
00:05:56,923 --> 00:05:58,870
This! This is my favorite, ensaymada!

117
00:05:58,922 --> 00:06:00,489
Give me five!

118
00:06:01,271 --> 00:06:02,844
Okay, let me get it for you!
Let me do it!

119
00:06:02,869 --> 00:06:06,929
I’m the business… oh okay,
I’ll just let him do it.

120
00:06:06,980 --> 00:06:07,980
You do it!

121
00:06:08,033 --> 00:06:09,193
Make sure everything’s good!

122
00:06:09,891 --> 00:06:10,891
Is it good?

123
00:06:10,916 --> 00:06:13,181
Of course, that’s our best seller!

124
00:06:13,665 --> 00:06:15,768
Of course, yeah!
We also have fruity ensaymada.

125
00:06:15,793 --> 00:06:17,081
You can have this.

126
00:06:17,668 --> 00:06:18,668
On the house.

127
00:06:18,693 --> 00:06:19,775
Really?!

128
00:06:19,999 --> 00:06:22,046
Mmm! Thank you, Andy!

129
00:06:22,071 --> 00:06:23,860
- You’re welcome!
- You know what, you look just as good!

130
00:06:25,024 --> 00:06:26,772
Anyways, let’s catch up soon!

131
00:06:26,797 --> 00:06:29,763
- Send me a chat, okay? Bye bye!
- Of course, bye! See you!

132
00:06:29,856 --> 00:06:31,365
- Mmmwaaahh!
- Take care!

133
00:06:34,128 --> 00:06:36,245
- Tash!
- Send her a chat!

134
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:38,453
She’s the one
I used to tell you about!

135
00:06:38,733 --> 00:06:39,946
I had a huge crush on her!

136
00:06:39,971 --> 00:06:41,902
Oh, right. I remember.

137
00:06:42,016 --> 00:06:45,529
You used to be drop-dead crazy about her.
Like drop dead!

138
00:06:45,843 --> 00:06:47,542
I don’t get it! Too flirty!

139
00:06:47,735 --> 00:06:50,708
You’re softer than a marshmallow!

140
00:06:52,471 --> 00:06:55,515
Do you guys think
she likes me too?

141
00:06:55,819 --> 00:06:57,526
I dont care, kuya!

142
00:06:57,860 --> 00:07:02,967
I will list down what you took,
you’re getting charged for that.

143
00:07:02,992 --> 00:07:05,171
Because it is not free!

144
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:08,907
So, Orb? What do you think?

145
00:07:09,524 --> 00:07:10,818
Do you think she likes me too?

146
00:07:11,668 --> 00:07:13,035
- Oh… Um.
- What do you think?

147
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:15,678
Maybe.
Maybe she likes you, too!

148
00:07:17,802 --> 00:07:19,302
She looks like she’s affected.

149
00:07:19,361 --> 00:07:20,361
What did I do?

150
00:07:20,685 --> 00:07:21,805
I don’t know. Not my problem.

151
00:07:21,837 --> 00:07:23,057
Pay what you owe.

152
00:07:23,082 --> 00:07:25,050
I don’t have anything to pay with,
what am I gonna do about it?

153
00:07:25,075 --> 00:07:26,075
Just go. Take care!

154
00:07:26,901 --> 00:07:28,081
You’re too much!

155
00:07:31,708 --> 00:07:32,828
Hey, friend!

156
00:07:32,939 --> 00:07:35,072
What a pleasant surprise!
How are you doing?

157
00:07:35,194 --> 00:07:39,757
Hi Cha! Nothing,
I just missed our baking class.

158
00:07:39,782 --> 00:07:41,744
I just missed you. How are you?

159
00:07:42,152 --> 00:07:45,604
Nothing much, thinking of
what else to try to make bigger sales.

160
00:07:45,637 --> 00:07:49,164
Isn’t the bakery making
great sales already?

161
00:07:49,189 --> 00:07:50,848
Not really.

162
00:07:51,205 --> 00:07:52,565
I don’t know, it’s Aga.

163
00:07:52,598 --> 00:07:54,704
Why?! Are you breaking up with Aga?!

164
00:07:54,764 --> 00:07:55,764
No!

165
00:07:55,786 --> 00:07:57,999
What the heck are you saying?!
It’s just a problem with the bakery.

166
00:07:58,024 --> 00:08:03,908
Recently, Aga’s solutions
are not translating into sales.

167
00:08:03,961 --> 00:08:06,581
But don’t get me wrong, he means well.

168
00:08:06,935 --> 00:08:16,978
But if what he's doing isn’t working,
what if you just support him, then?

169
00:08:17,438 --> 00:08:19,718
Even if it’s the opposite of what I like?

170
00:08:19,985 --> 00:08:21,792
That’s what you call reverse psychology.

171
00:08:22,098 --> 00:08:26,997
You make them feel as if
they thought of your idea.

172
00:08:27,030 --> 00:08:30,270
Do you really think that’s effective?

173
00:08:31,211 --> 00:08:32,485
David!

174
00:08:33,424 --> 00:08:35,297
Say hi to my friend!

175
00:08:35,397 --> 00:08:36,397
Hi!

176
00:08:37,005 --> 00:08:41,219
Baby, Cha is so pretty, right?

177
00:08:43,305 --> 00:08:46,152
I feel so ugly!

178
00:08:46,640 --> 00:08:49,859
No, baby,
you’re very beautiful in my eyes!

179
00:08:52,303 --> 00:08:54,943
It is effective!

180
00:08:55,622 --> 00:08:56,908
I’ll try that!

181
00:08:59,505 --> 00:09:00,505
That’s it!

182
00:09:01,931 --> 00:09:04,897
Wait, wait, what is that?
You still haven’t finished that?!

183
00:09:05,909 --> 00:09:09,443
Um, Lola Maxi,
that just got out of the oven!

184
00:09:09,468 --> 00:09:12,881
I’m not saying your bread
doesn’t taste good.

185
00:09:13,105 --> 00:09:15,890
What I’m saying is that maybe
you wanna try something new?

186
00:09:15,915 --> 00:09:20,177
New product, new marketing style!

187
00:09:20,202 --> 00:09:22,242
I know what you mean,
and that’s okay with me.

188
00:09:22,267 --> 00:09:25,964
What I’m saying now is that we
need to save money, don’t you think?

189
00:09:26,551 --> 00:09:27,551
Well okay then.

190
00:09:27,576 --> 00:09:29,822
All I’m thinking is that
maybe our customers

191
00:09:29,846 --> 00:09:32,093
won’t have any exciting
reasons to come back.

192
00:09:32,126 --> 00:09:33,673
Don’t you think, Cha?

193
00:09:35,423 --> 00:09:40,417
Maybe this is a good opportunity
to use reverse psychology or wait?

194
00:09:40,814 --> 00:09:44,127
Maybe I can call it Re-Pers psychology!

195
00:09:45,187 --> 00:09:46,187
Hey!

196
00:09:46,320 --> 00:09:47,513
- What? Lola!
- Cha!

197
00:09:47,538 --> 00:09:49,616
No, he’s right!

198
00:09:50,598 --> 00:09:51,798
Aga is right!

199
00:09:52,006 --> 00:09:54,713
Whatever he wants, we’ll do that!

200
00:09:56,218 --> 00:09:57,545
Oh, wait a minute.

201
00:09:57,570 --> 00:10:00,531
Why is the wind suddenly
blowing the opposite direction?

202
00:10:00,791 --> 00:10:02,191
No, Lola Maxi!

203
00:10:02,234 --> 00:10:05,307
It’s called supporting your husband!

204
00:10:07,542 --> 00:10:08,542
Really, now?

205
00:10:09,593 --> 00:10:12,146
I really don’t know about you two!

206
00:10:16,827 --> 00:10:17,928
- Hello!
- Hi, Ate Cha!

207
00:10:17,953 --> 00:10:19,461
How’s our sales?

208
00:10:19,492 --> 00:10:20,838
It’s fairly okay, Ate Cha.

209
00:10:20,863 --> 00:10:22,431
- It’s doing great!
- My loves!

210
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:24,400
Have you finished doing our ledgers?

211
00:10:26,823 --> 00:10:28,263
I forgot about that!

212
00:10:28,923 --> 00:10:32,684
I reminded you
lots of times already!

213
00:10:33,613 --> 00:10:34,713
Remember, Cha!

214
00:10:34,866 --> 00:10:36,852
Re-Pers psychology!

215
00:10:39,488 --> 00:10:42,489
Well, every one of us is busy,
aren’t we?

216
00:10:42,674 --> 00:10:44,967
I for one,
I still need to make a list.

217
00:10:45,307 --> 00:10:48,167
I still need to go to
the bakery supply store.

218
00:10:48,314 --> 00:10:51,951
But don’t worry, my love,
I’ll take care of it.

219
00:10:52,136 --> 00:10:53,136
No!

220
00:10:53,161 --> 00:10:55,533
No, I’ll take care of it.

221
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:01,388
I’ll do it, but wait a second,
I thought of a thing

222
00:11:02,062 --> 00:11:03,897
and I wanted to consult with you.

223
00:11:04,328 --> 00:11:08,224
How about let’s make this
bakery run for 24 hours?

224
00:11:08,709 --> 00:11:10,204
What? I mean, wow!

225
00:11:10,499 --> 00:11:11,499
24 hours?!

226
00:11:12,041 --> 00:11:14,547
That’s a good idea, my love!

227
00:11:14,853 --> 00:11:17,247
Maybe we do have a late
night market, you know?

228
00:11:17,272 --> 00:11:18,815
What do you think,
Chard, Iskineport?

229
00:11:18,921 --> 00:11:20,021
Do you think that’s okay?

230
00:11:20,234 --> 00:11:21,961
We’ll start tomorrow!

231
00:11:22,011 --> 00:11:23,538
That’s such a good idea!

232
00:11:23,563 --> 00:11:24,842
- No, wait, wait, wait, wait!
- What?

233
00:11:25,572 --> 00:11:26,572
Are you sure about this?
It doesn’t sound right.

234
00:11:26,692 --> 00:11:28,847
We’re gonna have to do
shifting hours. I need to

235
00:11:28,878 --> 00:11:33,423
sit down and think about
a business plan, okay?

236
00:11:33,810 --> 00:11:36,729
I’ll fix this first.
You wait for me, my love.

237
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:37,980
What do you mean…?

238
00:11:38,630 --> 00:11:40,250
Wait, I’ll get my stuff.

239
00:11:40,275 --> 00:11:41,966
- Chard, come here!
- What is that?

240
00:11:43,002 --> 00:11:44,795
- Did you hear that?
- You know,

241
00:11:44,820 --> 00:11:49,928
I can’t believe that Ate Cha
agrees to the boss’ weird ideas.

242
00:11:49,953 --> 00:11:53,313
I think Ate Cha is not on our side.

243
00:11:53,338 --> 00:11:55,531
She doesn’t want to do this anymore.
So why are we pushing forward?

244
00:11:55,557 --> 00:11:56,857
Okay, let’s think about it first.

245
00:11:56,860 --> 00:11:58,736
Let's find a new boss.

246
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:01,746
I know someone.
We’re going to apply there!

247
00:12:01,987 --> 00:12:04,645
Okay, just remember,
you should shave before we leave.

248
00:12:05,081 --> 00:12:06,334
You look like you’re
about to become a monkey.

249
00:12:09,302 --> 00:12:11,583
Sisters! It’s Chef K!

250
00:12:12,039 --> 00:12:13,352
Oh! Chef K…

251
00:12:30,578 --> 00:12:31,578
I know

252
00:12:32,768 --> 00:12:35,448
you all know that
I’m the one lending money here.

253
00:12:36,958 --> 00:12:40,618
And I know you’re all there!

254
00:12:41,041 --> 00:12:42,535
On the count of three,

255
00:12:43,447 --> 00:12:45,181
if no one comes out of hiding,

256
00:12:46,069 --> 00:12:50,225
I will raise your
debt interest to 10%!

257
00:12:50,766 --> 00:12:51,766
One!

258
00:12:52,258 --> 00:12:53,818
- Two!
- Chef K!

259
00:12:53,843 --> 00:12:55,548
Chef K, how long have
you been standing there?

260
00:12:55,573 --> 00:12:56,896
Actually, we’ve been
looking all over for you!

261
00:12:58,001 --> 00:13:03,570
Chef K, can I pay in kind?

262
00:13:04,063 --> 00:13:05,783
I don’t have cash
on me right now.

263
00:13:06,563 --> 00:13:07,656
You’re not my type!

264
00:13:08,173 --> 00:13:09,220
Oh! I know!

265
00:13:10,195 --> 00:13:11,635
Jasmine is your type!

266
00:13:12,117 --> 00:13:13,277
Jasmine who?

267
00:13:13,302 --> 00:13:14,521
A sack of Jasmine rice!

268
00:13:14,546 --> 00:13:17,033
Get him one! Am I right?!

269
00:13:17,058 --> 00:13:18,811
No! I don’t want that!

270
00:13:18,892 --> 00:13:24,650
Oh, hey! Chef K,
you look so handsome today!

271
00:13:24,675 --> 00:13:28,970
Maybe you wanna replace
your phone’s tempered glass?

272
00:13:29,267 --> 00:13:30,267
Let’s get you the mirror kind!

273
00:13:30,268 --> 00:13:33,955
So you can see your very
handsome face everyday!

274
00:13:35,798 --> 00:13:37,091
Oh stop it.

275
00:13:38,596 --> 00:13:39,596
Alright!

276
00:13:40,826 --> 00:13:42,286
I’ll take care of it and save everyone!

277
00:13:43,388 --> 00:13:45,321
I will solve all your problems!

278
00:13:45,411 --> 00:13:50,260
Listen, I can carry five hundred
pounds at a time for a hundred reps,

279
00:13:50,291 --> 00:13:51,867
you think I can’t carry
this weighty problem?

280
00:13:51,993 --> 00:13:53,873
Wow, that’s strong!

281
00:13:55,231 --> 00:13:56,231
- Goms!
- Yes?

282
00:13:56,256 --> 00:13:58,678
- Fan me!
- Fan him, fan him!

283
00:13:58,703 --> 00:13:59,980
Alright, everyone fall in line!

284
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:03,406
Let’s all talk about your collateral!

285
00:14:04,207 --> 00:14:06,386
Think about what you can give!

286
00:14:08,126 --> 00:14:10,111
- What is this?
- It’s Jasmine!

287
00:14:11,270 --> 00:14:12,270
Look inside!

288
00:14:12,883 --> 00:14:13,996
Where are they?

289
00:14:16,064 --> 00:14:17,738
Look, there’s no one here!

290
00:14:18,228 --> 00:14:20,795
You know, back in the day,
that was the dream for me –

291
00:14:21,025 --> 00:14:22,147
– but you know, life happened,
and I didn’t get to pursue it –

292
00:14:22,198 --> 00:14:23,829
There! What are you doing?!

293
00:14:23,888 --> 00:14:24,961
- Why, what’s up?
- Where were you?

294
00:14:24,985 --> 00:14:26,420
I’ve been looking all over for you!
There’s nobody here.

295
00:14:26,445 --> 00:14:27,445
We were just here!

296
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:29,002
Cha and I are going somewhere,

297
00:14:29,026 --> 00:14:32,345
so we need someone to stay
and watch the house and the… the…

298
00:14:32,370 --> 00:14:33,517
Where are you going?

299
00:14:33,703 --> 00:14:35,790
There’s just something we need to
take care of, something we need to buy.

300
00:14:35,815 --> 00:14:37,300
- Okay, I’ll hold the fort.
- See, that’s what I mean.

301
00:14:38,664 --> 00:14:41,035
I just want to introduce
to you my friend, Tara.

302
00:14:41,323 --> 00:14:43,463
Hi, Kuya Aga! Nice to meet you!

303
00:14:43,558 --> 00:14:44,925
Nice to meet you, Tara!

304
00:14:45,407 --> 00:14:46,560
Where did you two meet?

305
00:14:46,585 --> 00:14:51,628
Oh, he came to me, and then he told me
he wanted to learn how to do tattoos.

306
00:14:52,140 --> 00:14:53,140
Tat–tattoo?

307
00:14:53,835 --> 00:14:57,621
Oh! I thought you guys…
met in a church or something.

308
00:14:57,646 --> 00:14:59,590
Just because she looks like this?

309
00:14:59,615 --> 00:15:02,633
- Oh, no! Not at all.
- You look like you aren’t convinced!

310
00:15:02,999 --> 00:15:03,999
Hang on.

311
00:15:04,364 --> 00:15:05,364
Mmm.

312
00:15:05,423 --> 00:15:06,643
Tattoo!

313
00:15:06,668 --> 00:15:08,300
She’s a tattoo artist, and
an excellent one at that!

314
00:15:08,325 --> 00:15:09,325
See!

315
00:15:09,912 --> 00:15:13,079
They call me Talented Tara!

316
00:15:14,407 --> 00:15:15,707
Talented Tara!

317
00:15:15,732 --> 00:15:18,793
I just assumed a little.

318
00:15:18,818 --> 00:15:20,412
Well, we do get assumptions
about us a lot.

319
00:15:20,584 --> 00:15:24,161
You see tattooed people
like they’re bad people!

320
00:15:24,186 --> 00:15:26,175
Don’t you know this is art,

321
00:15:26,199 --> 00:15:30,038
and this has been in our culture
since our ancestors?

322
00:15:30,063 --> 00:15:31,462
Well, that’s true! I mean it’s all okay –

323
00:15:31,487 --> 00:15:33,117
But you were just talking
about a church!

324
00:15:33,142 --> 00:15:35,332
Take it seriously
if you wanna get a tattoo!

325
00:15:35,357 --> 00:15:36,511
And why are you planning
to learn how to do tattoos?!

326
00:15:36,536 --> 00:15:38,480
Apo Whang-Od is my idol!

327
00:15:39,032 --> 00:15:41,452
She’s really old,
but she still does tattoos!

328
00:15:41,572 --> 00:15:42,912
And you know what,

329
00:15:42,976 --> 00:15:44,582
I need to have a sideline,

330
00:15:44,922 --> 00:15:49,421
because I want to pursue
being a tattoo artist!

331
00:15:50,068 --> 00:15:52,068
Since when have you been
a tattoo artist?

332
00:15:52,093 --> 00:15:54,558
A long time ago. Don’t touch it!

333
00:15:54,641 --> 00:15:56,335
We all have our own dreams.

334
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:58,578
You have a dream, so do I!

335
00:15:59,527 --> 00:16:03,292
Hey! Nice, Orbs! Nice drip!

336
00:16:04,554 --> 00:16:06,228
- Go like this!
- What’s this?

337
00:16:06,998 --> 00:16:08,011
Oops, pass out!

338
00:16:09,302 --> 00:16:11,435
- Nice one!
- You’re silly.

339
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:12,800
You’re right.

340
00:16:12,825 --> 00:16:17,116
Actually, Keila and I
are meeting later.

341
00:16:17,571 --> 00:16:19,031
I didn’t know
you were serious about Kayla.

342
00:16:19,468 --> 00:16:23,312
You know I’ve had the biggest
crush on her for the longest time.

343
00:16:23,488 --> 00:16:25,697
So when she sent me
a message to meet up,

344
00:16:25,721 --> 00:16:27,172
you know I took the chance!

345
00:16:27,858 --> 00:16:29,985
Wow, Andres!

346
00:16:30,704 --> 00:16:31,944
Do you know that, come here…

347
00:16:32,328 --> 00:16:33,328
- That what?
- Come closer.

348
00:16:33,681 --> 00:16:36,233
You’re something else,
aren’t you?! Andres,

349
00:16:36,301 --> 00:16:40,420
- What?
- Who’s watching the bakery with me?

350
00:16:41,270 --> 00:16:43,696
- My shadow?
- Please, sister, please!

351
00:16:43,987 --> 00:16:44,987
Just let me have this.

352
00:16:45,040 --> 00:16:46,810
- And you know what…
- I’ll owe you one! Please!

353
00:16:46,835 --> 00:16:48,255
watch yourself over Keila.

354
00:16:48,315 --> 00:16:49,315
I know her.

355
00:16:49,532 --> 00:16:51,472
She appears to be kind when
she needs something from you.

356
00:16:51,958 --> 00:16:53,685
Oh wow, Anne.

357
00:16:53,881 --> 00:16:57,780
Hi, so right now,
we’re here at Bake Haus of U!

358
00:16:58,081 --> 00:16:59,314
Andy, say hi!

359
00:16:59,590 --> 00:17:00,590
- Hi!
- Hi!

360
00:17:00,615 --> 00:17:02,288
Andy’s sister, say hi!

361
00:17:02,303 --> 00:17:03,771
- Tash.
- What?

362
00:17:03,796 --> 00:17:05,434
- Tash.
- Oh, Tash?

363
00:17:05,459 --> 00:17:06,640
Hi, Tash!

364
00:17:06,665 --> 00:17:09,543
Um, employee, say hi!

365
00:17:09,568 --> 00:17:12,021
Hey, this is Anne.
She’s not an employee here.

366
00:17:12,052 --> 00:17:13,658
Oh, really?

367
00:17:13,818 --> 00:17:16,552
I’m sorry, my eyes failed to
recognize your plain clothes.

368
00:17:17,258 --> 00:17:20,363
Anyways, Andy, I’m so thirsty.
Do you have water or any drink?

369
00:17:20,461 --> 00:17:21,974
Ah, yeah, we do.

370
00:17:21,999 --> 00:17:23,778
- You do?
- Here, we have calamansi juice!

371
00:17:23,803 --> 00:17:26,809
- Okay!
- Let’s just bring it with us, then?

372
00:17:26,834 --> 00:17:27,834
- Yes, please!
- Let’s go!

373
00:17:27,859 --> 00:17:29,229
Thank you! Bye!

374
00:17:29,254 --> 00:17:30,254
Bye, guys!

375
00:17:31,244 --> 00:17:34,071
Well, Keila got her free stuff again!

376
00:17:34,586 --> 00:17:38,938
I’m gonna list this down
on Andres’ growing bill!

377
00:17:39,586 --> 00:17:41,226
I didn’t know his type was like that!

378
00:17:41,894 --> 00:17:43,727
Flirty little chicks!

379
00:17:45,671 --> 00:17:47,957
Well, what about you? What’s your type?

380
00:17:48,669 --> 00:17:52,189
Your super handsome friend?

381
00:17:54,244 --> 00:17:55,477
Tash! That’s gross!

382
00:17:56,357 --> 00:17:57,451
We’re not like that.

383
00:17:57,645 --> 00:17:59,078
Andres and I are just bros.

384
00:17:59,749 --> 00:18:01,770
Alright then, but for the record,

385
00:18:02,537 --> 00:18:03,691
I’m rooting for you.

386
00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:08,238
You’re prettier than Keila,
just try and glam up sometimes!

387
00:18:08,628 --> 00:18:10,195
Okay, let’s just put it this way,
I’ll give you a makeover!

388
00:18:10,588 --> 00:18:11,721
- Come here!
- Make over?

389
00:18:11,886 --> 00:18:12,946
Let’s start with this.

390
00:18:13,412 --> 00:18:14,412
- Lip gloss!
- What is that?

391
00:18:14,430 --> 00:18:15,430
Just use it! Use it!

392
00:18:15,455 --> 00:18:16,768
It’s giving me the creeps!

393
00:18:16,793 --> 00:18:17,793
Just try it!

394
00:18:18,101 --> 00:18:22,059
Hold it up like this,
pucker your lips and glide it on!

395
00:18:22,165 --> 00:18:23,294
You can do it!

396
00:18:23,319 --> 00:18:25,070
- Are you sure?
- I am!

397
00:18:25,095 --> 00:18:26,095
My love…

398
00:18:27,806 --> 00:18:28,873
Thank you, my love.

399
00:18:28,898 --> 00:18:29,911
Those are lots of eggs!

400
00:18:29,936 --> 00:18:32,425
You didn’t need to
come with me, but...

401
00:18:32,449 --> 00:18:33,706
let me carry that for you.

402
00:18:33,731 --> 00:18:35,917
Listen to yourself!
I’ll always come with you.

403
00:18:36,153 --> 00:18:38,420
I’ve been wondering
why you were carrying this.

404
00:18:38,444 --> 00:18:39,599
I’ll carry it for you!

405
00:18:39,936 --> 00:18:41,483
What will I do without you?

406
00:18:43,796 --> 00:18:44,796
Chef K!

407
00:18:45,502 --> 00:18:46,695
- Chef K!
- Hey, Aga!

408
00:18:46,820 --> 00:18:48,273
I didn’t know you were here,
what do we have here?

409
00:18:48,298 --> 00:18:49,805
Asking everybody to pay up!

410
00:18:50,429 --> 00:18:52,459
Look, the lines have gone way back there!

411
00:18:52,484 --> 00:18:54,860
Everyone’s giving collateral,
they’re giving what they can.

412
00:18:54,885 --> 00:18:56,853
Look at this one, he’s giving eggs.

413
00:18:58,113 --> 00:18:59,393
That should be money!

414
00:18:59,488 --> 00:19:00,728
I loaned them money!

415
00:19:01,198 --> 00:19:03,219
I’m glad we’ve sorted ours.

416
00:19:03,565 --> 00:19:04,604
You got that right.

417
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:07,880
Borta!

418
00:19:08,253 --> 00:19:09,253
- What?
- Come here!

419
00:19:10,970 --> 00:19:12,903
Come inside, I want to talk to you!

420
00:19:13,096 --> 00:19:14,109
Don’t you owe me money?

421
00:19:14,737 --> 00:19:18,965
Um, Chef K, I’m sorry,
I just got fired last night.

422
00:19:19,147 --> 00:19:22,287
Ooooh! Liar!

423
00:19:22,985 --> 00:19:25,425
Weren’t you just dancing all night
at the Star Horse Bar?

424
00:19:25,558 --> 00:19:27,451
Yeah, I just got fired last night.

425
00:19:27,483 --> 00:19:28,918
- Last night?
- Yeah.

426
00:19:30,579 --> 00:19:32,079
Look, I can’t have that!

427
00:19:32,179 --> 00:19:33,232
- Chef,
- Yeah?

428
00:19:33,257 --> 00:19:37,609
I just realized…
my friend isn’t like this.

429
00:19:37,634 --> 00:19:41,354
My friend, Chef K, he’s a nice guy.

430
00:19:42,681 --> 00:19:43,774
He’s patient.

431
00:19:44,328 --> 00:19:49,011
He gives everyone a second chance.

432
00:19:50,037 --> 00:19:51,160
Thank you!

433
00:19:51,185 --> 00:19:53,401
I really think you’re going
to give him a second chance.

434
00:19:53,561 --> 00:19:55,020
You’re gonna give
him another chance.

435
00:19:55,044 --> 00:19:57,495
My goodness! No,
what are you doing to me?!

436
00:19:57,520 --> 00:19:58,520
Okay, let’s just settle it like this.

437
00:19:58,541 --> 00:20:01,252
Excuse me. Borta, Borta, come here.

438
00:20:01,932 --> 00:20:03,139
Look at this guy’s body.

439
00:20:03,798 --> 00:20:05,765
- It’s small!
- Look at your body.

440
00:20:06,613 --> 00:20:07,893
You have the same built.

441
00:20:08,154 --> 00:20:11,071
Why don’t you just settle
this in an arm wrestling fight?

442
00:20:11,638 --> 00:20:12,711
You got it!

443
00:20:16,013 --> 00:20:18,345
- Chef K, you got this in the bag!
- They know you’re strong!

444
00:20:18,370 --> 00:20:20,682
This is your chance, I’ll take care of it!

445
00:20:20,802 --> 00:20:23,081
If you defeat him, your debt is paid.

446
00:20:25,956 --> 00:20:29,068
But if you lose, you give him
another chance, of course.

447
00:20:29,093 --> 00:20:30,781
- What? I don’t think that’s fair!
- Do you think that’s right?

448
00:20:30,841 --> 00:20:32,421
That’s right, that’s right!

449
00:20:34,874 --> 00:20:37,967
Chef K, Chef K, Chef K!

450
00:20:39,953 --> 00:20:42,015
On the count of three! Listen well!

451
00:20:42,586 --> 00:20:44,833
3, 2, 1, go!

452
00:20:56,761 --> 00:20:58,154
Give it up, give it up!

453
00:20:58,647 --> 00:21:00,504
If you give it up, your debt is paid!

454
00:21:00,535 --> 00:21:03,687
Come on, give it up! Give it up!

455
00:21:19,363 --> 00:21:21,660
Anne, get some ice, quick!

456
00:21:21,724 --> 00:21:23,171
What happened, Uncle K?

457
00:21:23,697 --> 00:21:24,744
I think I broke my arm.

458
00:21:26,452 --> 00:21:27,452
What is that on your lip?!

459
00:21:27,836 --> 00:21:31,410
Is that lip gloss or
did you eat lechon?!

460
00:21:32,281 --> 00:21:33,861
- Hey!
- Hey, Chef K!

461
00:21:33,886 --> 00:21:35,453
- Chef K!
- What are you doing here?

462
00:21:35,965 --> 00:21:38,623
- Are you a spy?!
- No! I’m not a spy, Chef K!

463
00:21:38,834 --> 00:21:40,194
Do you have anything I can work for?

464
00:21:41,760 --> 00:21:45,660
If I didn’t have any injury,
I would FPJ you!

465
00:21:46,079 --> 00:21:48,859
Uh, Chef K, I’m not joking.
I’m serious.

466
00:21:48,993 --> 00:21:53,670
We have a situation in the bakery,
we’re losing sales.

467
00:21:53,698 --> 00:21:57,060
Our boss, we don’t understand
his logic anymore.

468
00:21:57,085 --> 00:21:58,453
So do you maybe have
something I can work on?

469
00:22:02,514 --> 00:22:08,170
Anne, do you think it’s a good idea
if I give this moron a chance?

470
00:22:08,563 --> 00:22:11,665
If Bake Haus of U
loses their people,

471
00:22:11,822 --> 00:22:13,642
they’re not gonna
be able to produce bread!

472
00:22:13,886 --> 00:22:16,439
If they lose their bread,
they’re gonna lose their business.

473
00:22:16,561 --> 00:22:19,551
If they lose their business,
their love for each other is going to fade!

474
00:22:20,024 --> 00:22:23,241
If their love for each other fades,
Aga is gonna get lost!

475
00:22:23,266 --> 00:22:25,016
Cha is finally going to be mine!

476
00:22:25,183 --> 00:22:26,183
Am I right?

477
00:22:26,303 --> 00:22:28,003
That was kind of intense, Uncle K.

478
00:22:28,561 --> 00:22:31,681
Maybe we wanna go non-chalant?

479
00:22:32,161 --> 00:22:34,454
He was just looking for a sideline.

480
00:22:35,169 --> 00:22:36,216
Hmm?

481
00:22:38,219 --> 00:22:39,425
- You’re right.
- Huh?

482
00:22:40,431 --> 00:22:41,991
You came to the right person!

483
00:22:42,016 --> 00:22:43,016
Oh, my!

484
00:22:43,213 --> 00:22:44,213
I got you.

485
00:22:44,295 --> 00:22:45,821
- Oh, thank you!
- Come here.

486
00:22:45,846 --> 00:22:48,695
For your first task,
you’re going to make a poster.

487
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:49,720
- Poster?
- Yes, poster.

488
00:22:49,745 --> 00:22:51,341
We have an on-going promo,
it’s called BOGO.

489
00:22:51,366 --> 00:22:52,622
- Something like this?
- That’s it!

490
00:22:52,646 --> 00:22:53,656
Oh, BOGO!

491
00:22:53,681 --> 00:22:58,060
We have a Buy One
Get One on our pandesal!

492
00:22:58,085 --> 00:23:00,439
Oh thank you, thank you, boss!
Thank you!

493
00:23:00,464 --> 00:23:02,378
Oh, sorry, sorry, boss, sorry sorry!
Sorry, boss!

494
00:23:02,403 --> 00:23:03,621
Watch where you’re going!
Get out of my face

495
00:23:03,645 --> 00:23:05,033
or else I might end up
hurting you! Go on, get!

496
00:23:10,026 --> 00:23:11,126
That was a good idea.

497
00:23:11,466 --> 00:23:12,466
That really was!

498
00:23:13,124 --> 00:23:15,974
- BOGO… BOGO.
- Get ready.

499
00:23:16,687 --> 00:23:19,174
Iskineport, why can’t I sit down?

500
00:23:19,199 --> 00:23:21,207
I have to apologize
for now, Chard,

501
00:23:21,231 --> 00:23:25,246
since I used to be a mechanic
before I dreamed of being a –

502
00:23:25,329 --> 00:23:27,109
Ow! Ow!

503
00:23:28,219 --> 00:23:31,165
You have so much hair
by your belly button!

504
00:23:31,190 --> 00:23:34,046
It’s even a little dirty, it looks like
it’s going to be used to change oil!

505
00:23:34,801 --> 00:23:39,618
Ow, ow, ow! Ouch, Iskineport!

506
00:23:39,734 --> 00:23:41,848
My love, this is great!

507
00:23:42,089 --> 00:23:46,056
I’ve finished everything,
and then I just need to polish

508
00:23:46,080 --> 00:23:50,048
a few more things on the bookkeeping,
and then we can go.

509
00:23:50,741 --> 00:23:51,759
I’ll take care of everything.

510
00:23:52,855 --> 00:23:56,528
Oh wow, looks like Re-Pers
Psychology is really effective.

511
00:23:56,684 --> 00:23:58,791
Am I using it just enough,
or maybe a little too much?

512
00:23:59,755 --> 00:24:01,163
As Spiderman said,

513
00:24:01,193 --> 00:24:04,788
“with great power comes
great responsibility!”

514
00:24:06,422 --> 00:24:07,422
Who are you?!

515
00:24:08,301 --> 00:24:09,948
Who else but your conscience!

516
00:24:15,954 --> 00:24:18,180
My love, that’s enough.

517
00:24:18,542 --> 00:24:19,775
I’ll help you with it.

518
00:24:19,800 --> 00:24:21,506
- What?
- I’ll help you with that.

519
00:24:21,531 --> 00:24:26,179
No, it’s fine.
I said I’ll do it, so I’ll do it.

520
00:24:27,331 --> 00:24:30,450
- My love, you didn’t want that.
- What?

521
00:24:30,475 --> 00:24:35,824
I’ve been using Re-Pers psychology
on you the whole day.

522
00:24:36,144 --> 00:24:37,677
What is Re-Pers psychology?

523
00:24:37,979 --> 00:24:42,779
I’ll say something,
but you’re gonna do the opposite.

524
00:24:42,972 --> 00:24:48,753
I was trying to convince you to do
a different strategy for our bakery,

525
00:24:49,429 --> 00:24:55,302
but when I got you to do what I wanted,
I used it for other things as well.

526
00:24:55,327 --> 00:24:56,327
My love.

527
00:24:56,773 --> 00:24:57,946
My love, my love, my love.

528
00:24:59,085 --> 00:25:02,493
I know what Re-Pers psychology is,
I know what it means,

529
00:25:02,527 --> 00:25:05,261
it’s just that,
maybe I need to do this

530
00:25:05,285 --> 00:25:08,488
at least, to prove to you
that I can do all these.

531
00:25:08,990 --> 00:25:10,332
- My love…
- Hmm?

532
00:25:10,818 --> 00:25:12,591
I’m a simple person.

533
00:25:13,100 --> 00:25:15,746
I don’t need that
reverse psychology thing.

534
00:25:15,771 --> 00:25:17,099
You don’t need to work that on me.

535
00:25:17,339 --> 00:25:19,478
You know, my dream
for our lives is simple –

536
00:25:19,538 --> 00:25:20,971
for us to live comfortably,

537
00:25:21,040 --> 00:25:25,748
that we’re able to eat three times a day,
our children our happy, you are happy.

538
00:25:26,033 --> 00:25:28,918
Those are my desires, and I will
do everything to make it happen.

539
00:25:29,025 --> 00:25:33,962
That’s my dream for
our family, too, my love.

540
00:25:35,377 --> 00:25:36,784
- I’m sorry.
- Hmm!

541
00:25:36,843 --> 00:25:38,963
I’m gonna make it up to you.
I promise!

542
00:25:39,423 --> 00:25:40,860
- There’s no such thing as making it up!
- Hmmm?

543
00:25:40,967 --> 00:25:42,221
When you’re wrong, you’re wrong!

544
00:25:42,246 --> 00:25:45,395
As Chef K said,
every bad deed goes punished!

545
00:25:45,454 --> 00:25:46,454
So, go ahead!

546
00:25:46,878 --> 00:25:49,020
- Don’t fight it!
- Here? Okay, here!

547
00:25:50,073 --> 00:25:51,086
That’s too much!

548
00:25:51,117 --> 00:25:52,117
Oh you!

549
00:25:52,638 --> 00:25:54,935
I’m not used to this! It’s like…

550
00:25:54,985 --> 00:25:56,708
One more, another one!
Kiss me here!

551
00:25:56,893 --> 00:25:58,573
Don’t surprise me like that!

552
00:25:59,066 --> 00:26:00,199
Okay, we’re good?

553
00:26:00,224 --> 00:26:01,702
- Yes! We’re good!
- What?

554
00:26:01,727 --> 00:26:03,147
- Okay, I’ll go shower!
- You’re gonna go shower?

555
00:26:03,172 --> 00:26:04,172
Yes!

556
00:26:04,378 --> 00:26:05,846
Okay! Bye, my love!

557
00:26:05,871 --> 00:26:06,871
We’re good!

558
00:26:07,036 --> 00:26:08,343
Shower? You’re gonna go shower?

559
00:26:09,216 --> 00:26:10,269
It hurts!

560
00:26:11,398 --> 00:26:13,624
- There you go!
- Better?

561
00:26:13,649 --> 00:26:17,747
That’s the proof that your
training for level one is done!

562
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:19,160
Level one?!

563
00:26:19,366 --> 00:26:21,546
Do we have other levels?!

564
00:26:21,571 --> 00:26:22,571
Yes… twelve.

565
00:26:22,606 --> 00:26:24,799
You look like you’re
already so comfortable.

566
00:26:24,833 --> 00:26:27,353
Do you really need to be on the
lap when you’re doing my tattoo?

567
00:26:28,346 --> 00:26:29,526
Of course!

568
00:26:33,158 --> 00:26:34,276
- Ow!
- Oh!

569
00:26:34,382 --> 00:26:35,382
Iskineport!

570
00:26:35,517 --> 00:26:37,664
Hey, kuya. It’s Tara.

571
00:26:37,921 --> 00:26:41,200
- Tara, yeah. Tara.
- Hello! He has a new tattoo!

572
00:26:41,248 --> 00:26:42,248
Here, look!

573
00:26:42,549 --> 00:26:46,276
And also, Kuya,
I wanted to tell you something.

574
00:26:46,301 --> 00:26:47,301
Yeah, what is it?

575
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:54,168
I’m too embarrassed to say this,
but I think it’s time for us to part ways.

576
00:26:55,223 --> 00:26:56,223
What?

577
00:26:57,128 --> 00:26:58,128
Part...

578
00:26:58,235 --> 00:26:59,235
why?

579
00:26:59,328 --> 00:27:04,422
Because, Kuya, it seems like you’ve
changed the way you run your business.

580
00:27:04,447 --> 00:27:09,725
I’ve been thinking of a way… of other
things that could be my career, so…

581
00:27:09,750 --> 00:27:11,674
- Okay.
- I wanted to say my goodbyes.

582
00:27:11,699 --> 00:27:14,255
Hold on, one second.
I’m getting caught off guard.

583
00:27:14,280 --> 00:27:15,285
I feel like my…wait a moment.

584
00:27:15,792 --> 00:27:18,718
My love, I’m gonna use
Re-Pers psychology on him.

585
00:27:18,743 --> 00:27:20,624
- Mm-hmm.
- What? Okay? Okay.

586
00:27:22,761 --> 00:27:25,524
Iskineport, I hear you.

587
00:27:25,784 --> 00:27:30,125
Okay, since Charlene and I have talked
about this, okay, your decision is right.

588
00:27:30,426 --> 00:27:32,039
- Okay.
- Okay, thank you!

589
00:27:32,064 --> 00:27:34,076
I really wanna be a tattoo artist.

590
00:27:34,224 --> 00:27:35,444
- We’re gonna part ways now?
- Mm-mm.

591
00:27:36,859 --> 00:27:38,711
Why does it feel like it’s not working?

592
00:27:38,736 --> 00:27:40,516
Re-Pers psychology
isn’t some kind of magic.

593
00:27:40,541 --> 00:27:42,593
Maybe he likes it
better straightforward?

594
00:27:42,633 --> 00:27:44,223
Straightforward? Okay!

595
00:27:45,869 --> 00:27:48,623
Okay, push through
with your decision.

596
00:27:49,047 --> 00:27:50,380
- You may leave.
- What?

597
00:27:50,686 --> 00:27:52,206
Yeah! It’s all good!

598
00:27:52,414 --> 00:27:54,109
You can handle us being apart?!

599
00:27:54,134 --> 00:27:57,034
- Yeah, of course!
- You’re not going to stop me?

600
00:27:57,059 --> 00:27:58,059
Nope.

601
00:27:58,091 --> 00:28:01,403
Oh wow, you’re too much,
I’ve spent a lot of time here in the…

602
00:28:01,428 --> 00:28:02,428
Ssshh, iskineport!

603
00:28:02,828 --> 00:28:05,460
Tattoo artists don’t cry! Okay?

604
00:28:06,131 --> 00:28:07,990
Pain! We’re used to pain!

605
00:28:08,015 --> 00:28:09,043
We’re used to this?

606
00:28:09,576 --> 00:28:10,576
Yeah, yeah!

607
00:28:15,728 --> 00:28:17,302
Hey. Tara you look like you’re
about to bite me like a snake!

608
00:28:17,327 --> 00:28:20,111
Earlier you showed me you’re snake,
and now you’re the snake out to bite me.

609
00:28:20,291 --> 00:28:21,291
That’s so nice!

610
00:28:21,839 --> 00:28:23,486
Your face looks so rosy –

611
00:28:23,511 --> 00:28:26,683
Andy, thank you so much,
I had a great time!

612
00:28:26,708 --> 00:28:28,688
You are so welcome, Kayla.

613
00:28:29,835 --> 00:28:33,441
By the way,
I wanted to tell you –

614
00:28:33,466 --> 00:28:35,085
Wait, wait! Me first!

615
00:28:37,238 --> 00:28:38,603
Keila,

616
00:28:39,181 --> 00:28:40,711
um…I like you.

617
00:28:41,495 --> 00:28:42,815
May I court you?

618
00:28:43,565 --> 00:28:45,030
Oh…

619
00:28:45,380 --> 00:28:48,641
I-I’m sorry. Andy.

620
00:28:49,642 --> 00:28:56,944
I only date guys with 300K followers,
and I think yours is right around 2K only?

621
00:29:01,123 --> 00:29:04,509
Yeah, but I thought the reason
why we went out was because –

622
00:29:04,557 --> 00:29:06,200
Ah, that’s what I was going to say.

623
00:29:06,374 --> 00:29:11,406
I wanted to ask you if you would be a dear
and lend me your whole place for a day.

624
00:29:11,606 --> 00:29:12,786
I wanted to make some content.

625
00:29:13,455 --> 00:29:15,959
Don’t worry,
I’ll pay you via free publicity,

626
00:29:15,984 --> 00:29:17,840
and then I’ll also promote
your store on my page!

627
00:29:18,317 --> 00:29:19,544
Excuse me, Keila.

628
00:29:19,643 --> 00:29:21,817
They don’t need your free publicity.

629
00:29:22,078 --> 00:29:25,740
We’re not going to put our
operations on hold for your vlog.

630
00:29:26,157 --> 00:29:31,109
Sorry, I’m the business-focused sister,
remember?

631
00:29:31,489 --> 00:29:33,442
Oh, well, your loss.

632
00:29:33,942 --> 00:29:34,942
Bye, Andy!

633
00:29:36,803 --> 00:29:40,777
Hmmm! I feel like,
I want those cute muffins!

634
00:29:40,802 --> 00:29:42,440
- They’re good, aren’t they?
- Yeah! Can I have some?

635
00:29:42,465 --> 00:29:44,301
That’s called Kabayan!
It’s ten pesos a piece!

636
00:29:44,326 --> 00:29:45,326
Kabayan?

637
00:29:45,351 --> 00:29:46,633
For ten a piece? I don’t have cash.

638
00:29:46,727 --> 00:29:47,727
Andy?

639
00:29:48,486 --> 00:29:49,553
Oh, sorry.

640
00:29:50,018 --> 00:29:52,444
We’re still closed. We’re closed.

641
00:29:52,469 --> 00:29:55,280
Mmm. Okay! Bye!

642
00:29:55,981 --> 00:29:56,981
Bye!

643
00:29:59,845 --> 00:30:04,792
Didn’t I tell you, Keila is a user.

644
00:30:04,950 --> 00:30:06,497
This is on you!

645
00:30:07,150 --> 00:30:09,263
Why don’t you wake up
and see reality?!

646
00:30:10,204 --> 00:30:11,290
I told you, Orb!

647
00:30:11,328 --> 00:30:12,777
Keila has been like that, since.

648
00:30:13,658 --> 00:30:16,192
Especially since
she became an influencer.

649
00:30:16,295 --> 00:30:18,249
She thinks she’ll get
everything for free.

650
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:19,880
Exactly.

651
00:30:20,028 --> 00:30:21,028
Come to think of it,

652
00:30:21,232 --> 00:30:25,171
she’s been to the shop a few times,
but she never paid!

653
00:30:25,371 --> 00:30:27,071
Not a single peso, at that!

654
00:30:28,570 --> 00:30:30,630
I don’t know what to say.

655
00:30:32,407 --> 00:30:33,407
This is saddening.

656
00:30:34,240 --> 00:30:36,413
I’m not an influencer,

657
00:30:36,793 --> 00:30:41,825
but I’ll treat you,
just so you forget all this.

658
00:30:42,525 --> 00:30:44,432
How does fishball
by the court sound?

659
00:30:45,563 --> 00:30:46,563
Game!

660
00:30:47,986 --> 00:30:48,986
Are you wearing lipgloss?!

661
00:30:49,453 --> 00:30:50,453
Wait a second…

662
00:30:51,919 --> 00:30:54,085
Oh, this? Tash lent me hers.

663
00:30:54,573 --> 00:30:56,484
- I just tried it on.
- Really?

664
00:30:56,842 --> 00:30:58,557
Doesn’t it look so good on her!
She looks so pretty and plump!

665
00:30:58,581 --> 00:30:59,843
Not at all pale!

666
00:30:59,898 --> 00:31:01,724
She’s right! It suits you so well!

667
00:31:02,551 --> 00:31:03,551
Let’s go!

668
00:31:18,365 --> 00:31:19,365
Tara.

669
00:31:19,833 --> 00:31:20,833
Let’s go!

670
00:31:21,358 --> 00:31:24,011
You know what,
my decision to leave is right.

671
00:31:24,471 --> 00:31:25,844
I’ll go with you to your province.

672
00:31:26,354 --> 00:31:28,721
You’ll teach me more
about doing tattoos,

673
00:31:28,745 --> 00:31:31,111
and I’ll pursue my dream there
to be a tattoo artist, okay?

674
00:31:31,518 --> 00:31:33,928
- Of course.
- Nobody can stop me from my decisions.

675
00:31:33,964 --> 00:31:37,691
No matter what happens,
you and I are going to your province.

676
00:31:38,091 --> 00:31:39,091
Let’s go.

677
00:31:41,547 --> 00:31:42,547
Iskineport!

678
00:31:42,987 --> 00:31:44,353
- Hi, Tara.
- Kuya Aga.

679
00:31:44,431 --> 00:31:45,431
Are you really leaving?

680
00:31:45,944 --> 00:31:46,944
Yes, Kuya.

681
00:31:47,047 --> 00:31:49,140
And nobody can stop me.

682
00:31:49,307 --> 00:31:50,517
Look, I understand where
you’re coming from.

683
00:31:50,542 --> 00:31:51,834
But how about our friendship,
don’t you think

684
00:31:51,858 --> 00:31:53,151
you’re throwing all
that away all too easily?

685
00:31:53,528 --> 00:31:54,688
Don’t correct me.

686
00:31:55,414 --> 00:31:56,454
So, all that meant nothing–

687
00:31:56,479 --> 00:31:58,756
- Nothing! I’m leav–
- I loved you!

688
00:32:00,315 --> 00:32:01,315
I love you!

689
00:32:01,815 --> 00:32:03,022
So, nothing?
You’re gonna leave me just like that?

690
00:32:04,736 --> 00:32:06,362
Leave me, Tara. Go home.

691
00:32:06,579 --> 00:32:08,653
My kuya and I are staying.
We’re going to live here.

692
00:32:08,731 --> 00:32:10,939
He nurtured me and took care of me.
So, leave.

693
00:32:11,047 --> 00:32:13,081
Oh, is that so? That easily?

694
00:32:13,369 --> 00:32:15,909
I trained you, and then
just like that, goodbye?

695
00:32:16,148 --> 00:32:17,148
How about this?!

696
00:32:18,963 --> 00:32:19,963
Why?!

697
00:32:21,082 --> 00:32:22,276
That’s not mine!

698
00:32:22,309 --> 00:32:23,222
That’s impossible–

699
00:32:23,402 --> 00:32:24,402
I’m kidding.

700
00:32:24,465 --> 00:32:26,585
I thought you were pregnant!
My goodness!

701
00:32:26,739 --> 00:32:28,445
- No…
- You scared me, Tara!

702
00:32:28,483 --> 00:32:31,461
I just want to say that it’s good
that you two are okay again.

703
00:32:31,486 --> 00:32:33,240
- Thank you.
- I’ll just call you

704
00:32:33,265 --> 00:32:35,449
when I’ve got extra clients
and when you’re free.

705
00:32:35,638 --> 00:32:37,109
- Okay.
- Come tattoo with me.

706
00:32:37,282 --> 00:32:38,933
- Okay?
- Hopefully it’s still me, okay?

707
00:32:38,958 --> 00:32:40,803
- Of course!
- Well is that so? Then go with her!

708
00:32:41,383 --> 00:32:42,923
You’re allowing me to?

709
00:32:42,948 --> 00:32:44,904
You’re just coming when
she needs an extra pair of hands!

710
00:32:45,024 --> 00:32:46,643
Tara, maybe you should go now.

711
00:32:48,136 --> 00:32:49,136
Thank you, Tara!

712
00:32:54,588 --> 00:32:59,113
Kuya, I don’t understand you!
You’re asking me to leave and go with Tara!

713
00:32:59,340 --> 00:33:00,627
You’re confusing me.

714
00:33:00,689 --> 00:33:02,482
Wow, there are so many of them!

715
00:33:02,526 --> 00:33:03,786
Thank you, come again!

716
00:33:03,961 --> 00:33:04,961
Good?

717
00:33:04,986 --> 00:33:07,268
Hey, Anne! That’s perfect!

718
00:33:07,381 --> 00:33:08,381
Gosh!

719
00:33:12,171 --> 00:33:13,318
These suckers!

720
00:33:14,624 --> 00:33:17,637
- Oh, hi, Chef K!
- Hi!

721
00:33:17,662 --> 00:33:21,078
Chef K, you know what,
I didn’t come here for you.

722
00:33:21,251 --> 00:33:24,590
I came for the pandesal promo!

723
00:33:24,615 --> 00:33:26,543
- Wow! Perfect!
- Why?!

724
00:33:26,674 --> 00:33:28,627
Is Chard done with the poster?

725
00:33:29,702 --> 00:33:33,512
See! The Buy One Get is effective,
isn’t it?

726
00:33:33,537 --> 00:33:37,019
That’s true, Chef K!
But you know what’s more effective?

727
00:33:37,286 --> 00:33:40,152
- What?
- The buy one get ten promo!

728
00:33:42,718 --> 00:33:44,644
Te- that’s supposed to be get one!

729
00:33:45,144 --> 00:33:46,786
- Get ten, get ten!
- Chard!

730
00:33:46,811 --> 00:33:48,465
- Hey! Boss?!
- Come here!

731
00:33:48,873 --> 00:33:50,786
- Buy one get one!
- And?

732
00:33:51,012 --> 00:33:52,012
Why is this ten?!

733
00:33:52,789 --> 00:33:58,005
So it’s much more, I made this,
what’s better than one?! Ten!

734
00:34:00,272 --> 00:34:01,974
- You made it to ten?
- I did!

735
00:34:02,013 --> 00:34:03,600
You’re such an idiot!

736
00:34:03,625 --> 00:34:05,859
Why did you make it ten, I said just one!

737
00:34:06,037 --> 00:34:07,037
You idiot!

738
00:34:07,062 --> 00:34:08,062
Well, ten is right

739
00:34:08,087 --> 00:34:11,200
because that’s the number of bones
in your body I’m gonna break!

740
00:34:11,225 --> 00:34:13,598
Ow! Ow, help me! Help!

741
00:34:15,022 --> 00:34:16,622
So, that’s what happened.

742
00:34:17,184 --> 00:34:18,824
Now, you know the story.

743
00:34:19,543 --> 00:34:21,811
Hang on, turn that off.

744
00:34:22,376 --> 00:34:24,329
Let’s go back to the tattoo thing.

745
00:34:24,961 --> 00:34:26,421
I’m not against anything for you guys.

746
00:34:26,446 --> 00:34:27,600
You’re old enough
to think for yourselves.

747
00:34:27,960 --> 00:34:31,579
If you wanna get tattoos,
if you wanna get tattoos,

748
00:34:31,953 --> 00:34:33,759
- that’s fine with me.
- It’s up to you.

749
00:34:33,784 --> 00:34:35,361
But, but, hear me out.

750
00:34:35,386 --> 00:34:37,538
You should think about it well.

751
00:34:37,563 --> 00:34:40,519
Because, that will forever be
literally etched on your skin.

752
00:34:40,857 --> 00:34:43,083
We know, Dad, Mom.

753
00:34:43,883 --> 00:34:46,146
But, we don’t have any plans to.

754
00:34:47,206 --> 00:34:49,406
The one who’s actually
getting the tattoo is…

755
00:34:50,891 --> 00:34:53,975
Aaaaaaaah! Stop!
Iskineport, ow, ow, ow!

756
00:34:54,000 --> 00:34:55,368
Lola Maxi!

757
00:34:55,659 --> 00:34:58,446
Iskineport!
What are you doing to Lola Maxi?!

758
00:34:59,523 --> 00:35:02,919
I’m drawing a tattoo for her on her
rear leg, I just went to the comfort room.

759
00:35:02,944 --> 00:35:05,248
When I came out,
she was running out already!

760
00:35:05,273 --> 00:35:07,409
- Tattoo?!
- She has a sputnik tattoo on her butt!

761
00:35:07,556 --> 00:35:09,042
- What?! Lola Maxi!
- Yeah!

762
00:35:09,067 --> 00:35:13,985
I used to be a commando,
and a sputnik courted me.

763
00:35:14,010 --> 00:35:17,370
When I said yes to him,
I went sputnik too, hence the tattoo!

764
00:35:17,395 --> 00:35:18,915
Okay, then let’s get the
other leg a different tattoo!

765
00:35:18,940 --> 00:35:21,041
Oh, no, no! No, it hurts!

766
00:35:21,228 --> 00:35:23,248
Iskineport, Lola Maxi
doesn’t want one anymore.

767
00:35:24,253 --> 00:35:25,313
Mmm, hang on. Hang on a second.

768
00:35:25,338 --> 00:35:27,334
This is still rolling, let’s say goodbye!

769
00:35:27,501 --> 00:35:28,948
- Alright, alright!
- Let’s say goodbye!

770
00:35:28,973 --> 00:35:30,898
Come, come!

771
00:35:31,013 --> 00:35:32,877
- What do we say?
- In… one… two…

772
00:35:32,902 --> 00:35:33,902
- Game!
- three!

773
00:35:33,946 --> 00:35:40,150
In every problem or happiness,
Pers is first, Pers is the hero!
